eal busy one. Mr. <a title="Srdjan Prodanovic" href="http://www.facebook.com/Some1Else">Some1Else</a> was in town and we were pulling off all-nighters for three days.</p>
<p>The result: a <strong>beautiful localized community app</strong>, complete with discussions, user projects and profiles, events and presentations.</p>
<p>It was inspired by the community app of the Boston’s <a title="Boston.rb" href="http://bostonrb.org/">Boston.rb</a>, which is also available as open-source on <a title="Boston.rb's community site on GitHub" href="http://github.com/bostonrb/bostonrb/">GitHub</a>. At first we forked it and were planning to just do some small modifications in logic and a new stylesheet, but it soon showed that our needs were a bit different.</p>
<p>That’s when we decided to start anew and while our app is still based on Boston’s we rewrote somewhere around 80% of the code.</p>
<p>Future plans include making a native event management system, with proper attending options and Google Maps. In the more near future we have to improve Boston’s Twitter fetching, as it is currently using search on twitter, which is not returning tweets from some users, for no apparent reason.</p>
<p>This is the current final result, wrapped in a slick package.</p>
